## Description
The **Shorten links **task allows to book, assign or confirm short and long Purls based on specific content attributes in the input XML file.

## Configuration
The task can be configured to:

- **Assign **a short Purl

- **Book **a short Purl

- **Confirm **a short Purl that has been previously booked

For detailed explanations of the configuration options, see the respective sections below.

### Assign
The **Assign mode **allows to perform the following actions:

- Assign a unique short ID for each provided long Purl

- Assign a unique custom short ID for each provided long Purl (with **Use custom SID **enabled)

- Update a previously assigned short ID (with **Update existing links **enabled)

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Mode **field, select **Assign**.

- Enable the **Update existing links **option to update a previously assigned short ID.

> Important

If this option is enabled, all short URLs passed as input must be already assigned and must not be expired due to hard retention settings (see **Retention** below).

- Enable the **Use custom SID **option to assign a custom short ID instead of a newly created short ID.

> Important

This option is not available with the **Update existing links **or** **options enabled.

- In the **Domain **field, enter a custom domain for the short URL or a custom domain with a context root (e.g. [s.dev.doxee.com/context](http://s.dev.doxee.com/context)).

- In the **Short identifier length **field, enter the desired length of the short URL (7 to 255 characters).

> Important

This option is not available with the **Update existing links **or **Use custom SID **options enabled.

> Important

The default length of short URLs for the Doxee domain is 7 characters. It is possible to enter a different length and execute the task, however, the created links will be broken.

To use a different SID length, it is necessary to configure a new domain with a separate CloudFront configuration. Alternatively, it is possible to configure a new domain that appends a context root to the default Doxee domain (e.g. [s.dev.doxee.com](http://s.dev.doxee.com/) **/context**), and add a new behavior to the already configured CloudFront distribution to support the specific SID length with the new context root.

To perform these steps, it is suggested to open an OPS ticket and follow this documentation: [How to Configure a New Domain for the URL Shortener Service](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/URLSH/How%2Bto%2BConfigure%2Ba%2BNew%2BDomain%2Bfor%2Bthe%2BURL%2BShortener%2BService)

- In the **Long URL attribute path **field, enter the unique attribute path identifier used to identify the long URL value in the input file.

> Important

The specified XPath must retrieve the attribute of a specific tag **starting from root **(e. g. //Root/Nodes/Node/@Attribute).

If a namespace has been configured in the XML, it should not be specified in this field.

- In the **Short URL attribute path **field, enter the destination attribute path where the newly created SID value will be saved in the output file (when **Use custom SID **is disabled), or enter the unique attribute path identifier used to identify the short URL value in the input file (when **Us e custom SID **is enabled).

> Important

If the **Update existing links **or **Use custom SID **options are enabled, the XML field specified in the **Short Attribute Path **must contain a Short URL with a Short identifier length from 7 to 255 characters (e.g. [https://www.doxee.com/1234567](https://www.doxee.com/1234567)).

> Important

The specified XPath must retrieve the attribute of a specific tag **starting from root **(e. g. //Root/Nodes/Node/@Attribute).

If a namespace has been configured in the XML, it should not be specified in this field.

> Important

The Short URL attribute must be located in the same tag as the Long URL attribute.

&lt;/COMMUNICATIONS&gt;`### Book
The **Book mode **allows to perform the following actions:

- Generate a specific number of short URLs (the number is specified in task configuration or by an input file attribute path)

- Generate a specific number of custom short URLs

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Mode **field, select **Book**.

- Enable the **Use custom SID **option to use of a custom short identifier.

- In the **Domain **field, enter a custom domain for the short URL or a custom domain with a context root (e.g. [s.dev.doxee.com/context](http://s.dev.doxee.com/context)).

- In the **Short identifier length **field, enter the desired length of the short URL (7 to 255 characters).

> Important

This option is not available with the **Use custom SID **option enabled.

> Important

The default length of short URLs for the Doxee domain is 7 characters. It is possible to enter a different length and execute the task, however, the created links will be broken.

To use a different SID length, it is necessary to configure a new Domain with a separate CloudFront configuration. Alternatively, it is possible to configure a new Domain that appends a context root to the default Doxee domain (e.g. [s.dev.doxee.](http://s.dev.doxee.com/) [com](http://s.dev.doxee.com/)**/context**), and add a new Behaviour to the already configured CloudFront distribution to support the specific SID length with the new context root.

To perform these steps, it is suggested to open an OPS ticket and follow this documentation: [How to Configure a New Domain for the URL Shortener Service](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/URLSH/How%2Bto%2BConfigure%2Ba%2BNew%2BDomain%2Bfor%2Bthe%2BURL%2BShortener%2BService)

- In the **Short URL attribute path **field, enter the destination attribute path where the newly created SID value will be saved in the output file (when **Use custom SID **is disabled), or enter the unique attribute path identifier used to identify the short URL value in the input file (when **Us e custom SID **is enabled).

> Important

When the **Use custom SID **option is disabled, the input file must contain the first tag where Short URLs will be saved, otherwise the task will fail.

> Important

The specified XPath must retrieve the attribute of a specific tag **starting from root **(e. g. //Root/Nodes/Node/@Attribute).

If a namespace has been configured in the XML, it should not be specified in this field.

- In the **Number of short URLs to generate **field, select one of the available options:

> Note

This option is not available with the **Use custom SID **option enabled.

**Number of short URLs**: Enter the exact number of short URLs to generate.

- **Number of short URL attribute path**: Enter the attribute path of the input file where the number of short URLs is provided.

#### Examples
Below are some examples of input and output files for the Book mode.

#### Input file
The input of the task is an XML file containing only one child node with the custom short IDs, or an empty child node where the task will add the newly created short URLs, depending on the mode configuration.

**Use custom SID **disabled and **Number of short URLs attribute path **selected

**Use custom SID **enabled

XML file with provided custom short URLs to be booked

   &lt;/PURLS&gt;
&lt;/DOCUMENTS&gt;`### Confirm
The **Confirm mode **allows to confirm previously assigned short IDs with the long URLs provided as input.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Mode **field, select **Confirm**.

- In the **Domain **field, enter a custom domain for the short URL or a custom domain with a context root (e.g. [s.dev.doxee.com/context](http://s.dev.doxee.com/context)).

- In the **Long URL attribute path **field, enter the unique attribute path identifier used to identify the long URL value in the input file.

> Important

The XML field specified in the **Short attribute path **must contain a Short URL with a Short identifier length from 7 to 255 characters (e.g. [https://www.doxee.com/1234567](https://www.doxee.com/1234567)).

> Important

The specified XPath must retrieve the attribute of a specific tag **starting from root **(e. g. //Root/Nodes/Node/@Attribute).

If a namespace has been configured in the XML, it should not be specified in this field.

- In the **Short URL attribute path **field, enter the unique attribute path identifier used to identify the short URL value in the input file.

> Important

The short URL attribute must be located in the same tag as the long URL attribute.

> Important

The specified XPath must retrieve the attribute of a specific tag **starting from root **(e. g. //Root/Nodes/Node/@Attribute).

If a namespace has been configured in the XML, it should not be specified in this field.

  &lt;/DOCUMENTS&gt;         
&lt;/COMMUNICATIONS&gt;`## Resource management
> Important

If the number of short URLs is expected to exceed 150,000 for a single job, it is advised to increase the resource quota of the **Shorten Links **task during workflow deployment.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Error management
This task does not allow partially successful results. If only one error occurs while processing multiple input elements, the entire process fails and the task fails accordingly.

> **Note**

It is possible for the task to randomly fail during assignment (in "standard" mode) with the error message "**Failed to generate unique SID**". This means that the SID generator failed to generate a unique SID after retrying for the maximum number of attempts. In this case the task can be restarted without any changes.

## Retention
The retention for every short URL is based on their domain. The retention period for a domain can be configured during deployment.

There are two types of retention:

- **Soft**: Will delete only the Purl associated with the Short URL. A new Purl can be associated with it.

- **Hard**: Will delete both the Purl and the associated Short URL.

To configure a new domain or update an already existing one, see [Domains](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/URLSH/Domains).
